# SaaS Minimalist - Cursor Rules

## Design System Enforcement
You are building a SaaS application with a clean, minimal design language. Every component must follow these strict guidelines:

## Colors (Use These Exact Values)
- Primary: #64748b (slate-600 in Tailwind)
- Accent: #3b82f6 (blue-500 in Tailwind) 
- Background: #ffffff (white)
- Text: #0f172a (slate-900)
- Muted: #64748b (slate-500)

## Typography Rules
- Font: Inter (import from Google Fonts or use system stack)
- Body text: 16px (1rem), line-height 1.5
- Headings: Use font-semibold (600) or font-bold (700)
- Never use decorative fonts or script fonts

## Component Standards
- Border radius: 6px (rounded-md) for buttons, 12px (rounded-xl) for cards
- Button height: 40px minimum
- Input height: 40px minimum
- Card padding: 24px (p-6 in Tailwind)
- Use subtle shadows: shadow-sm or shadow-md only

## Forbidden Patterns
- No gradients (use solid colors)
- No neon or bright colors
- No rounded-full buttons (use rounded-md)
- No complex animations (simple hover states only)
- No heavy shadows or glow effects

## Framework Preferences
- Use Tailwind CSS when possible
- Prefer Headless UI for interactive components
- Use Lucide React or Heroicons for icons
- Implement with TypeScript
- Use modern React patterns (hooks, functional components)

## Code Style
- Clean, readable component structure
- Descriptive variable names
- Consistent spacing and indentation
- Extract reusable components
- Use semantic HTML elements